  "text": "Our neural language model is a recurrent network with a single 1000-dimensional GRU layer, which is trained on the target sides of our paral-1 http://www.statmt.org/wmt15/ lel corpora. The embedding size is 512 and we use a batch size of 100 to train the model. Before training the neural language model, we need to manipulate the training corpus to decompose words into morphemes for which we use Morfessor [CITATION_1] , an unsupervised morphological analyzer. Using Morfessor each word is segmented into different subunits where we consider the longest part as the stem of each word; what appears before the stem is taken as a member of the set of prefixes (there might be one or more prefixes) and what follows the stem is considered as a member of the set of suffixes.",
